IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: IMPROVE THE HEALTH & WELL-BEING OF UNDER- served populations by providing gov't purchased prepaid healthcare coverage to individuals covered under medicaid and other health progs.
IRS990.MissionDesc: TO IMPROVE THE HEALTH AND WELL-BEING OF UNDERSERVED POPULATIONS BY PROVIDING COMPREHENSIVE PREPAID HEALTHCARE COVERAGE TO MEDICAID, ESSENTIAL PLAN, HARP, CHILD HEALTH PLUS AND QUALIFIED HEALTH PLAN RECIPIENTS.
IRS990.Desc: MEDICAID MANAGED CARE: HEALTHFIRST PHSP, INC. (PHSP) IS A LICENSED PREPAID HEALTH SERVICES PLAN THAT PROVIDES COMPREHENSIVE PREPAID HEALTH CARE COVERAGE TO BENEFICIARIES OF GOVERNMENT HEALTH CARE COVERAGE PROGRAMS. PHSP HAS PARTICIPATED IN NEW YORK'S MEDICAID PROGRAM SINCE OCTOBER 1994. FOR 2016 THERE WERE 904,859 MEMBERS ENROLLED IN PHSP'S MEDICAID PLAN. PHSP'S NETWORK INCLUDES 71 REGIONAL HOSPITALS THAT PROVIDE SERVICES TO MEMBERS.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: ESSENTIAL PLAN (EP): HEALTHFIRST PHSP, INC. (PHSP) IS A LICENSED PREPAID HEALTH SERVICES PLAN THAT PROVIDES COMPREHENSIVE PREPAID HEALTH CARE COVERAGE TO BENEFICIARIES OF GOVERNMENT HEALTH CARE COVERAGE PROGRAMS. EP IS A NEW PROGRAM IN 2016 WHICH COVERS INDIVIDUALS WHO WOULD OTHERWISE BE ELIGIBLE FOR EITHER CERTAIN CATEGORIES OF EXPANDED MEDICAID COVERAGE OR SIGNIFICANT SUBSIDIES FOR QUALIFIED HEALTH PLAN (QHP) FOR LITTLE OR NO MEMBER CONTRIBUTION. FOR 2016 THERE WERE 117,546 MEMBERS ENROLLED IN PHSP'S EP PLAN. PHSP'S NETWORK INCLUDES 59 REGIONAL HOSPITALS THAT PROVIDE SERVICES TO MEMBERS.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: HEALTH AND RECOVERY PLAN (HARP): HEALTHFIRST PHSP, INC. (PHSP) IS A LICENSED PREPAID HEALTH SERVICES PLAN THAT PROVIDES COMPREHENSIVE PREPAID HEALTH CARE COVERAGE TO MEDICAID ELIGIBLE INDIVIDUALS THAT HAVE SERIOUS BEHAVIORAL HEALTH DIAGNOSES. THE HARP PROGRAM WAS INTRODUCED IN 2015 AND IS A MANAGED CARE PROGRAM WITHIN MEDICAID. FOR 2016 THERE WERE 17,159 MEMBERS ENROLLED IN PHSP'S HARP PROGRAM. PHSP'S NETWORK INCLUDES 62 REGIONAL HOSPITALS THAT PROVIDE SERVICES TO MEMBERS.

Essential Plan (EP) is a new program in 2016 which covers all of the essential health benefits covered under the Qualified Health Plans offered on the Marketplace and is offered to eligible individuals within specific income guidelines who are ineligible for Medicaid and do not have access to affordable employer coverage. FORM 990, PART III, LINE 4D OTHER PROGRAM SERVICES CHILD HEALTH PLUS (CHP): THE ORGANIZATION IS A LICENSED PREPAID HEALTH SERVICES PLAN THAT PROVIDES COMPREHENSIVE PREPAID HEALTH CARE COVERAGE TO CHP RECIPIENTS PURSUANT TO ARTICLE 44 OF THE NEW YORK STATE PUBLIC HEALTH LAW. PHSP HAS PARTICIPATED IN NEW YORK'S CHP PROGRAM SINCE 1997. Qualified Health Plans (QHP): In 2014, PHSP established a Qualified Health Plan ("QHP") under the Health Care Reform, which is certified by the New York State Health Insurance Marketplace ("Marketplace"). QHP provides essential health benefits, follows established limits on cost-sharing (deductible, copayment, and out-of-pocket maximum amounts), and must maintain compliance with other provisions of Health Care Reform. QHP is administered under an agreement between PHSP and the DOH that extends through December 31, 2018. BASIC HEALTH PLANS (BHP): HEALTHFIRST PHSP, INC. (PHSP) IS A LICENSED PREPAID HEALTH SERVICES PLAN THAT PROVIDES STANDARD HEALTH PLAN COVERAGE TO ELIGIBLE INDIVIDUALS WHO WOULD NOT HAVE ACCESS TO COVERAGE THROUGH THE HEALTH INSURANCE MARKETPLACE. PHSP UNDERTOOK NEW YORK'S BHP PROGRAM AS OF 2015. FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 3 HEALTHFIRST PHSP, INC. (PHSP) CONTRACTS WITH HF MANAGEMENT SERVICES, LLC (HFMS) TO PROVIDE ALL OF ITS MANAGEMENT AND ADMINISTRATIVE SERVICES. PHSP DOES NOT MAINTAIN ITS OWN STAFF OR OFFICE SPACE; THESE ARE PROVIDED BY HFMS. HFMS CHARGES A PERCENT OF PREMIUM ON A PER MEMBER PER MONTH BASIS OR A FLAT FEE PER MEMBER PER MONTH. THE ARRANGEMENT IS APPROVED BY RESOLUTION OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS AND THE NY STATE DEPARTMENT OF HEALTH. ALL OFFICERS, KEY EMPLOYEES, AND HIGHEST COMPENSATED EMPLOYEES WERE PAID BY, AND WORKED FOR HFMS, A MANAGEMENT COMPANY WHICH PROVIDES MANAGEMENT SERVICES FOR MULTIPLE ENTITIES. NONE OF THE INDIVIDUALS LISTED EARNED ANY COMPENSATION FROM PHSP.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 7B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE AMENDMENT OF THE ORGANIZATION'S GOVERNING DOCUMENTS IS SUBJECT TO THE APPROVAL OF HEALTHFIRST, INC. SOME OF THE DECISIONS OF THE GOVERNING BODY, SHOULD THEY OCCUR, ARE SUBJECT TO APPROVAL BY STATE REGULATORS: * DISTRIBUTION OF THE ORGANIZATION'S NET ASSETS * CERTAIN CHANGES TO PREMIUM RATES * EXPANSION TO OTHER MANAGED CARE BUSINESSES * SPECIFIC TYPES OF CHANGES TO THE ORGANIZATION'S BENEFIT PLANS * MANAGEMENT FEE RATE CHANGES [APPROVAL IS ALSO REQUIRED FROM THE MANAGEMENT COMPANY]

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE 990 IS PREPARED BY THE HF MANAGEMENT SERVICES, LLC (HFMS) CORPORATE FINANCE DEPARTMENT STAFF AND THEN REVIEWED BY THE HFMS VICE PRESIDENT, CONTROLLER AND TREASURER. SECONDARY REVIEWS ARE ALSO PERFORMED BY THE HFMS CHIEF LEGAL OFFICER AND CHIEF FINANCIAL OFFICER. THE DRAFT 990 IS THEN REVIEWED BY AN INDEPENDENT ACCOUNTING FIRM. THE DRAFT 990 IS THEN PRESENTED TO THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS FOR REVIEW. THE FINAL 990 IS SUBMITTED AFTER THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS REVIEW IT.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: A CONFLICT OF INTEREST DISCLOSURE STATEMENT IS COMPLETED ANNUALLY BY EACH BOARD MEMBER, OFFICER AND KEY EMPLOYEE. A NOMINATED BOARD MEMBER WHO DOES NOT COMPLETE THE STATEMENT WITHIN THE CALENDAR YEAR WILL NOT BE PERMITTED TO CARRY OUT DUTIES. THE SAME APPLIES TO AN OFFICER OR KEY EMPLOYEE WHO DOES NOT COMPLETE THE APPROPRIATE DISCLOSURES. ANY DISCLOSURE OF A CONFLICT OR POTENTIAL CONFLICT IS REVIEWED BY THE CHIEF COMPLIANCE OFFICER. CONFLICTS ARE ADDRESSED BY EXAMINING THE RELATIONSHIP OF THE INDIVIDUAL TO THE ORGANIZATION AND THE NATURE OF THE DISCLOSURE. A REPORT OF ANY CONFLICTS IS PREPARED FOR DISCUSSION WITH AUDIT AND COMPLIANCE COMMITTEE OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS OF HEALTHFIRST, INC., THE NOT FOR PROFIT CORPORATE PARENT, AS WELL AS THE FULL BOARD OF DIRECTORS OF HEALTHFIRST PHSP, INC. AS APPROPRIATE. GUIDANCE IS PROVIDED TO THE NECESSARY PARTIES AND ACTION IS TAKEN, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO DISCLOSURE AND RECUSAL FROM DECISION-MAKING, MODIFICATIONS TO BUSINESS AGREEMENTS, CHANGES IN VENDORS OR REPLACEMENT OF THE DIRECTOR, OFFICER OR KEY EMPLOYEE WITH A NON-CONFLICTED INDIVIDUAL.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: BECAUSE THE REPORTING ORGANIZATION DID NOT COMPENSATE ANY OFFICER OR EMPLOYEE, THE REPORTING ORGANIZATION HAS RESPONDED "NO." HOWEVER, THE COMPENSATION OF THE CEO, OTHER OFFICERS AND KEY EMPLOYEES IS DETERMINED BY THE COMPENSATION COMMITTEE OF HF MANAGEMENT SERVICES, LLC, THE MANAGEMENT COMPANY THAT PROVIDES ALL SERVICES TO PHSP (A RELATED ORGANIZATION). THE COMMITTEE CONSISTS ONLY OF HFMS MEMBER HOSPITAL DIRECTORS (WHO ARE NOT EMPLOYED NOR COMPENSATED BY HFMS OR ANY OF ITS AFFILIATES). THE PROCESS FOR DETERMINING COMPENSATION IS DESCRIBED IN THE COMMITTEES CHARTER. THE PROCESS INCLUDES ENGAGEMENT OF AN OUTSIDE HUMAN RESOURCES CONSULTING FIRM TO CONDUCT A COMPARABILITY ANALYSIS. THE ANALYSIS INCLUDES COMPARABLE RANGES OF EXECUTIVE COMPENSATION USING THE COMPANY'S INDUSTRY CLASSIFICATION. THE COMMITTEE MEETS PRIOR TO IMPLEMENTATION OF ANY CHANGE IN COMPENSATION. CONTEMPORANEOUS MINUTES OF EACH MEETING ARE PREPARED.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION MAKES ITS GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY, AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AVAILABLE TO THE GENERAL PUBLIC BY PROVIDING COPIES ON REQUEST FOR INSPECTION AT ITS CORPORATE OFFICES.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, SCHEDULE R, PART V, LINE 2
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: METHOD OF DETERMINING AMOUNT INVOLVED ITEM (1): THE AMOUNT REPRESENTS THE EXPENSES INCURRED AND PAID OR DUE TO THE RELATED ORGANIZATION FOR SERVICES RENDERED BASED ON CONTRACTED RATES APPROVED BY RESOLUTION OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS AND BY STATE REGULATORS. ITEM (2): IN 2016, PHSP PURCHASED 50% OF THE OUTSTANDING COMMON STOCK OF HEALTHFIRST INSURANCE COMPANY, INC. ("HFIC"), A SUBSIDIARY, IN EXCHANGE FOR CASH CONSIDERATION. ITEM (3): IN ACCORDANCE WITH THE ORGANIZATION'S CONTRACTUAL ARRANGEMENTS AND UPON APPROVAL BY THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS OF PHSP, HEALTHFIRST HEALTH PLAN, INC. ("HFHP"), AN AFFILIATED COMPANY AND HEALTHFIRST, CERTAIN MEMBER DEFICIT BALANCES IN PHSP MAY BE OFFSET BY A PERCENTAGE OF THAT MEMBER'S SURPLUS BALANCE IN HFHP THROUGH AN INTERCOMPANY TRANSFER; CONVERSELY, HFHP MEMBER DEFICIT BALANCES MAY BE OFFSET BY A PERCENTAGE OF PHSP'S SURPLUS BALANCES. IN 2016, THE ALLOWABLE AMOUNT OF SURPLUS OFFSET WAS INCREASED FROM 25% TO 50% OF SURPLUSES THAT MAY ACCRUE, AND WOULD OTHERWISE BE DISTRIBUTED TO A MEMBER HOSPITAL OR AFFILIATE INSTITUTION BY EITHER PHSP OR HFHP. ITEM (3) IS A TRANSFER FROM HFHP. ITEM (4): DURING 2016, HEALTHFIRST REQUESTED AND RECEIVED APPROVAL FROM THE DEPARTMENT OF HEALTH TO TRANSFER CAPITAL RESERVES FROM NHP TO PHSP. THIS TRANSFER IS IN CONJUNCTION WITH THE LIQUIDATION/DISSOLUTION OF THE NHP OPERATIONS.
